headline: Has GE Run Too Far After Pentagon Missile Push and Striking 77% Rally?
summary: If you have been watching General Electric lately, you are not alone. It is the kind of stock that gets people talking, especially after the ride shareholders have had in the past several years. Just this year, GE is up nearly 77% year to date, with an impressive 62% gain over the past twelve months. And if you zoom out a little further, the returns are jaw-dropping: up nearly 800% in five years. Clearly, something has shifted, and it's not just investor enthusiasm driving it. Recent...
